genresAdvancedInfo.name: minnesota metal
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Minnesota metal is a subgenre of heavy metal music that originated in the state of Minnesota, USA. Known for its aggressive and intense sound, it combines elements of thrash metal and death metal, characterized by fast guitar riffs, pounding drums, and growling vocals. This subgenre often showcases the technical prowess of musicians, creating a high-energy and headbanging experience for metal enthusiasts.
